description: Israel's parliament voted to ban a U.N. relief agency from operating in Israel, a move that could threaten aid work in Gaza as the war rages there. Iran's foreign ministry said Iran “will use all available tools” to deliver a response to Israel's airstrikes on Iranian military targets early Saturday. NBC News' Raf Sanchez reports.
title: Israel's parliament votes to ban a U.N relief agency in Israel

description: Secretary of State Antony Blinken arrived back in the United States just as Israel was striking Iran — its anticipated retaliation for a massive missile strike earlier this month.
title: An exhausted Antony Blinken can claim one win after Mideast trip, but also plenty of losses

description: Brown University suspended the pro-Palestine group after it protested the university's decision not to divest its endowment from companies that support Israel.
title: Brown University suspends its chapter of pro-Palestine student group

description: One person was killed and dozens were injured after a truck rammed a bus stop near Tel Aviv. The incident is suspected to be a terrorist attack. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez reports on the incident and the latest developments from the Middle East.
title: Suspected terror attack in Israel kills at least one person and injures dozens

description: Scientists have connected 800-year-old skeletal remains found in a well at Norway’s Sverresborg castle to a mysterious figure mentioned in a medieval Norse saga, using advanced DNA analysis.
title: Skeletal remains in a castle well lend credence to a centuries-old Norse saga

description: An NBC News team in Gaza met with a 6-year-old Palestinian girl who was featured in a viral video carrying her injured little sister along a Gaza street. Qamar Subuh was caught on camera carrying Sumaya, 5, back to the family's makeshift home in the Al Bureij refugee camp.
title: Video shows 6-year-old Gaza girl carrying her injured little sister

description: A year after armed militias launched a surprise joint offensive in northeastern Myanmar, the junta has lost huge swaths of territory it will struggle to regain.
title: Militia groups push military government close to the brink in Myanmar

description: The makeup of Japan’s future government was in flux after voters punished Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba’s scandal-tainted ruling coalition in a Sunday election.
title: Japan’s government in flux after election gives no party majority
